Create frontend/hooks/__tests__/use-intersection-observer.test.ts — tests for use-intersection-observer.ts.

Import: { renderHook, act } from '@testing-library/react'
Import: { useIntersectionObserver } from '../use-intersection-observer'

You need to mock IntersectionObserver globally. Before all tests:

let mockObserve: jest.Mock;
let mockDisconnect: jest.Mock;
let mockCallback: (entries: Partial<IntersectionObserverEntry>[]) => void;

beforeEach(() => {
  mockObserve = jest.fn();
  mockDisconnect = jest.fn();
  (global as any).IntersectionObserver = jest.fn((cb) => {
    mockCallback = cb;
    return { observe: mockObserve, disconnect: mockDisconnect, unobserve: jest.fn() };
  });
});

Test cases (describe 'useIntersectionObserver'):
1. 'returns initial state' — render hook, expect result.current.isIntersecting === false, result.current.entry === null
2. 'ref is a function' — expect typeof result.current.ref === 'function'
3. 'observes element when ref is set' — create a div, act(() => result.current.ref(div)), expect mockObserve to have been called
4. 'disconnects on unmount' — create div, set ref, unmount, expect mockDisconnect to have been called
5. 'updates isIntersecting when entry changes' — create div, set ref, then act(() => mockCallback([{ isIntersecting: true }])), expect result.current.isIntersecting === true

Max 45 lines. Use Jest + React Testing Library.

