STRICT: Max 30 lines. React 18+. Full JSDoc. Named export only.

Props interface (MUST export):
/** Props for Divider component */
export interface DividerProps {
  /** Orientation of the divider */
  orientation?: 'horizontal' | 'vertical';
  /** Optional label text displayed in the center */
  label?: string;
  /** Additional CSS class */
  className?: string;
  /** CSS color for the divider line */
  color?: string;
  /** Thickness in pixels (default: 1) */
  thickness?: number;
  /** Spacing/margin in pixels (default: 16) */
  spacing?: number;
}

Render:
- Wrapper: <div role="separator" className={`divider divider-{orientation} ${className || ''}`} style={...} aria-orientation={orientation}>
- Horizontal: style={{ borderTop: `{thickness}px solid {color || '#e5e7eb'}`, margin: `{spacing}px 0` }}
- Vertical: style={{ borderLeft: `{thickness}px solid {color || '#e5e7eb'}`, margin: `0 {spacing}px`, alignSelf: 'stretch' }}
- If label provided: <div class="divider-label" style={{display:'flex',alignItems:'center',gap:'8px'}}> with <span>{label}</span> between two <hr> elements styled with flex:1
- Defaults: orientation='horizontal', thickness=1, spacing=16

